      • translateAlternateColorCodes

        public static java.lang.String translateAlternateColorCodes(char alt_char,
                                                            java.lang.String string)
        Translates a string using an alternate color code character into a string that uses the internal ChatColor.COLOR_CHAR color code character. The alternate color code character will only be replaced if it is immediately followed by 0-9, A-F, a-f, K-O, k-o, R or r.

        Parameters:
        alt_char - The alternate color code character to replace. Ex: &
        string - Text containing the alternate color code character
        Returns:
        Text containing the ChatColor.COLOR_CODE color code character
        See Also:
        ChatColor.translateAlternateColorCodes(char, String)
